    <note>Li(2) Zhongshi [1013] His ancestors were originally Bozhou, Boping people, who moved to Daming, Neihuang xian and then again to Kaifeng. He was initially recommended by his father-in-law, Chen(1) Zhizhong [34]. One son-in-law Chen(1) Shixiu [80], was Zhizhong's nephew. Zhongshi was Lu(9) Gongzhuo's [7304] son-in-law and the father-in-law of Lu(9) Zhiwen [3645], Gongzhuo's [7304] grandson. His other son-in-laws were all from good bureaucratic lineages (liangshi). Qiang Zhi, WJ, 34.10b-14b; XCB, 175.5a-5b, 187.2a, 260.9a; SS, 331.4a-4b; YLDD, 12506.1b, 24a. CBD, 2, 955.</note>
